# Private Skills

This file is a TEMPLATE. Copy it into a public checkout at
`.cursor/rules/private-skills.mdc` when your private overlay is mounted. It is
git-ignored in the public toolkit (see the public `.gitignore`), so it is present
only when the overlay is in place — it never ships in the public repo.

It complements the tracked public router `.cursor/rules/shared-skills.mdc`
(which routes only the PUBLIC skills) by registering the PRIVATE skill whose
entire content — `SKILL.md` and products — lives only in the overlay.

Before starting a task that matches this workflow, read the relevant `SKILL.md`:

- Creating educational coding-interview practice solutions (problem statements, approach notes, algorithm/data-structure explanations, commented implementations, runnable test cases), especially under `interviews/company-specific/<company>/coding/`: `.agents/skills/coding-interview/SKILL.md`

The `coding-interview` skill is mounted by the overlay into
`.agents/skills/coding-interview` (via a symlink or clone). If that path is
absent, the overlay is not mounted and this router should not be present.

Edit skill content only in the overlay's canonical skill folder; do not replace
the compatibility symlinks under `.claude/skills` / `.cursor/skills` with copies.
